org.jcvi.jillion.internal.trace.chromat.ztr.data

Class DataHeader

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jcvi.jillion.internal.trace.chromat.ztr.data.DataHeader

  • public final class DataHeader
extends Object
    DataHeader contains the various supported ZTR 1.2 Header byte values which determines how a data block is encoded.
    Author:
    dkatzel

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      static Byte BYTE_DELTA_ENCODED
      Data header value specifying that this data block will be encoded as a (possibly multi level) delta encoding of byte values.
      static Byte FOLLOW_DATA_ENCODED
      Data header value specifying that this data block will be encoded using a computing most frequent follow symbol table.
      static Byte INTEGER_DELTA_ENCODED
      Data header value specifying that this data block will be encoded as a (possibly multi level) delta encoding of int values.
      static Byte RAW
      Data header value specifying that this data block will not be encoded (raw).
      static Byte RUN_LENGTH_ENCODED
      Data header value specifying that this data block will be encoded in run length encoding format.
      static Byte SHORT_DELTA_ENCODED
      Data header value specifying that this data block will be encoded as a (possibly multi level) delta encoding of short values.
      static Byte SHRINK_INTEGER_TO_BYTE_ENCODED
      Data header value specifying that this data block will be encoded to convert a signed int value into a byte value(assuming it fits).
      static Byte SHRINK_SHORT_TO_BYTE_ENCODED
      Data header value specifying that this data block will be encoded to convert a signed short value into a byte value(assuming it fits).
      static Byte ZLIB_ENCODED
      Data header value specifying that this data block will be compressed using zlib (probably Huffman).
